22:07.950 --> 22:12.670
or it's no big deal, but it, but there was a lot of human, human emotion and love

22:12.670 --> 22:13.450
and that sort of thing.

22:13.510 --> 22:14.350
And I hadn't seen it before.

22:14.490 --> 22:16.110
Have you been through first hand pregnancy?

22:16.470 --> 22:17.610
I mean, it's very realistically.

22:17.950 --> 22:18.270
Yes.

22:18.590 --> 22:18.850
Yes.

22:19.130 --> 22:19.250
Yes.

22:20.890 --> 22:24.110
Through the, through the pregnancy and through a miscarriage before it.

22:24.790 --> 22:27.930
So that I took all that and, you know, you write what you know.

22:27.930 --> 22:31.310
And so I put that in there because those were, those were very important times

22:31.310 --> 22:32.990
of my life when they happened.

22:33.690 --> 22:37.410
I was there when my daughter was born in the delivery room and that's why we got,

22:37.510 --> 22:40.850
you know, we got to have the, the big group scene when, when Serena is born.

22:41.090 --> 22:43.750
And I thought, you know, everybody ought to get to share this experience

22:43.750 --> 22:45.670
because it was really, it was really a lot of fun.

22:46.150 --> 22:50.970
And I, one of those, again, one of those gratifying things is to have a fan come

22:50.970 --> 22:55.050
up and say, you know, gee, I really liked, you know, female fans, especially.

22:55.270 --> 22:56.410
You really got that down.

22:56.410 --> 22:59.810
I really understand that our husbands come up and say, my wife was like

22:59.810 --> 23:00.650
that when she was pregnant.

23:02.510 --> 23:05.870
I mean, Joy makes a wonderful comment in there that he, you know, maybe women

23:05.870 --> 23:08.110
change species when they're pregnant.

23:08.830 --> 23:10.910
There's some biological basis for that.

23:11.450 --> 23:13.030
I read that all after my wife.

