23:21.050 --> 23:24.590
So I recommended these and told her it was a, it was really a love story,

23:24.630 --> 23:26.230
especially saying, well, she was just amazed.

23:26.230 --> 23:27.950
Science fiction could be a love story.

23:28.150 --> 23:28.650
Oh, really?

23:28.830 --> 23:29.930
And she's going to read it.

23:30.090 --> 23:34.810
So I'm anxious to see her reaction to it.

23:35.590 --> 23:36.430
Um, okay.

23:36.510 --> 23:37.290
I have a comment.

23:37.510 --> 23:41.190
So I'm going to, I'm going to, I say the series is a people story.

23:41.190 --> 23:42.310
It's not a hardware story.

23:42.710 --> 23:49.910
Uh, you don't, you don't explain your warps, uh, the ghosts, uh, how, why

23:49.910 --> 23:53.470
there's so many cross fertile bipeds around us, where they're just there.

23:53.910 --> 23:55.030
And we just accept that.

23:55.130 --> 23:56.930
And then I have parenthetically my applause.

23:57.510 --> 24:02.270
Um, do you consider, uh, okay.

24:02.330 --> 24:05.290
Did you ever think about explaining these things or you just decide,

24:05.930 --> 24:09.930
hang on, make this a science fiction book and we're not going to explain all

24:09.930 --> 24:14.470
this shit, how the, how we do this and that people know it's a book.

24:14.730 --> 24:19.810
So, yeah, I did what a great number of science fiction writers do.

24:19.930 --> 24:22.470
And that is, I, I built on what had gone before.

24:22.930 --> 24:26.870
And there was, there's, there's such a huge basis now of groundwork that has

24:26.870 --> 24:31.050
been done for us that we don't have to spend a lot of time explaining how

24:31.050 --> 24:32.750
this works and how that works.

24:33.070 --> 24:36.150
And, you know, oh, actually this warp takes us through techie on space,

24:36.290 --> 24:37.850
blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

24:38.090 --> 24:43.290
We can just use keywords, uh, and key concepts and the reader has already

24:43.290 --> 24:44.310
been grounded in that.

24:45.610 --> 24:49.290
And then you can spend more time telling the story instead of having more

24:49.290 --> 24:52.850
time, spend more time explaining all the, all the mechanical functions.

24:53.430 --> 24:57.570
Uh, there's a hard science, there's a big hard science story that I really

24:57.570 --> 25:00.370
want to write, but I don't think I have the skills yet as a writer to do it.

25:00.410 --> 25:05.430
So I'm saving that one for when I'm, when I'm better trained in my craft.

